g.text: Divisibility rules help determine if a number can be divided evenly by another without performing full division.

tr.td: Sum of digits is divisible by 3
Number formed by last two digits is divisible by 4
Double the last digit, subtract it from the rest of the number. If the result is divisible by 7, the original number is divisible by 7.
Number formed by last three digits is divisible by 8
Sum of digits is divisible by 9
Subtract the sum of the digits in odd positions from the sum of the digits in even positions. If the result is divisible by 11, the original number is divisible by 11.

ul.li: Divisibility rules provide shortcuts for checking divisibility.
Useful for simplifying fractions and understanding number properties.
